Package: blockclustr
Title: Performs block cluster randomization when units also need to be clustered
Version: 0.1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Erin",
           family = "Rossiter",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "erossite@nd.edu",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-4446-4272"))
Description: blockclustr performs block cluster randomization when units also need to be clustered, for example, when researchers are conducting experiments involving social interaction amongst participants who aren't naturally clustered into groups.
